Data Scientist		American Express		Greater New York City Area		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>American Express is working on our company’s next transformation—leverage big data/machine learning techniques to elevate value delivered to Customers.  As a Data Scientist, you will be part of a team dedicated to helping American Express accelerate its big data transformation. You will be challenged with designing winning applications and developing capabilities that will elevate American Express to the forefront of the big data revolution. </p><p>  </p><p>More particularly, this role will reside within the Commercial Data Science team. As a member of this team you will be expected to – </p><ul><li>Enhance the quality of existing commercial data </li><li>Create data elements that  capture new information or plug information gaps - Developing insights into customer behavior and introduce new approaches to transform complex behavioral data into actionable information </li><li>Evaluate new commercial data sources </li><li>Create new commercial capabilities </li><li>Transformation in decision making capabilities by exploring big data/machine learning techniques such as Random Forest, Gradient Boosting Machines, k-nearest neighbor, support vector machines and Text Mining/NLP </li><li>Intelligently integrating traditional structured data with unstructured data </li></ul><p>  </p><p><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline"> </span></strong> </p><p><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline">Qualification:</span></strong> </p><p><strong>Required:</strong> </p><ol><li>PhD/Master's Degree in quantitative field (e.g. Finance, Engineering, Physics, Mathematics and Economics) or MBA with quantitative background; </li><li>Excellent programming skills and comfort with data manipulation tools (eg: Java,Python, R, SAS, SQL, SPSS) </li><li>Prior experience working with very large datasets using Big Data tools and platforms (Hadoop, PIG/HIVE) is strongly preferred </li><li>Strong working knowledge of data mining techniques, including regression analysis, clustering, decision trees, SVM (support vector machines), GBM </li><li>Demonstrated ability to apply cutting edge statistical techniques to business problems and to leverage external thinking  (from academia and/or other industries) </li><li>Strong technical and analytical skills with the ability to apply both quantitative methods and business skills to create insights and drive results. </li><li>Knowledge of reviewing company financials and commercial bureau data is preferred</li></ol></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>American Express is a global service company, providing customers with exceptional access to products, insights and experiences that enrich lives and build business success.<br /> <br />Each day, American Express makes it easier, safer and more rewarding for consumers and businesses to purchase the things they need and for merchants to sell their goods and services. An engine of commerce, American Express provides innovative payment, travel and expense management solutions for individuals and businesses of all sizes. Most of all, we help our customers realize their dreams and aspirations through industry-leading benefits, access to unique experiences, business-building insights, and global customer care. We enable our customers to do and achieve more.<br /> <br />Learn more about us at: <br /><br />https://www.americanexpress.com/<br /> https://www.facebook.com/AmericanExpressUS<br /> http://www.foursquare.com/americanexpress<br /> https://twitter.com/americanexpress<br /> https://www.youtube.com/user/AmericanExpress<br /> <br />See our community guidelines at:<br /> <br />http://amex.co/guidelineslinkedin<br /> <br />If you have a customer service issue or question, please visit www.americanexpress.com/contactus</p></div>